        content: "Have you ever listened to yourself speak and noticed how often you say 'um,' 'uh,' or 'like'? These small words, called filler words, can significantly undermine your credibility and clarity as a debater.\n\nFiller words are verbal placeholders we use when our mouths are moving faster than our brains. While they're natural in casual conversation, in competitive debate they can make you seem unprepared, nervous, or uncertain about your arguments.\n\nIn this lesson, you'll learn to identify common filler words, understand why we use them, and master techniques to replace them with powerful pauses. By the end, you'll have practical strategies to make your speaking cleaner and more persuasive.",
